        <div class="accent-padding">
          <h3 class="accent nm">Alpaca Fleece vs. Sheep's Wool</h3>
          <p>Although similar, there are a few key differences between wool and alpaca fleece that prove that alpaca fleece is the ultimate animal fiber.</p>
          <h5 class="nmb line-accent">Warmer than Sheep's Wool</h5>
          <p>Unlike sheep's wool, alpaca fibers are completely hollow. This creates greater thermal capacity and allows for more warm air to fill the textile.</p>
          <h5 class="nmb line-accent">Hypoallergenic</h5>
          <p>Alpaca fibers do not contain Lanolin, which is found in sheep's wool. Lanolin tends to irritate many people upon contact.</p>
          <h5 class="nmb line-accent">Moisture Wicking</h5>
          <p>Because alpaca fibers are hollow, they trap more heat and naturally push water away. Water essentially evaporates due to the structure and warmth of the alpaca fiber. In comparison, sheep's wool will absorb up to 50% of its body weight.</p>
